A series of explosions rocked the Sinai desert, targeting tourists in Taba and other resorts.
The blasts, including a car bomb at the Hilton hotel, left over 100 people dead or injured.
Despite warnings, Israelis continued to visit the popular holiday destination.
Israeli intelligence had previously foiled a plot by Palestinian militants.
The attacks coincided with a major Israeli offensive in Gaza.
Egypt and Israel cooperated in evacuating Israeli tourists from the area.
The incidents underscored ongoing security concerns in the region, emphasizing the need for peace and cooperation.
